SIMPLE: stent
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stent
<hw>Stent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>Obs.
imp.</pos> <conjf>Stente</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>obs. p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Stent</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[See <er>Stint</er>.]</ety> <def>To
keep within limits; to restrain; to cause to stop, or cease; to
stint.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then would he weep, he might not be <qex>stent</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Yet n'ould she <qex>stent</qex>⟦br⟧
Her bitter railing and foul revilement.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Stent
<hw>Stent</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To stint; to stop; to
cease.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And of this cry they would never <qex>stenten</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Stent
<hw>Stent</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An allotted portion; a stint.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Attain'd his journey's <xex>stent</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Mir. for
Mag.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stenting</ent>⟦br⟧
